---
By: Ramana Maharshi
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 430
    Verse: 16
Tags:
  - Silence
---
The only language able to express the wholeness of truth is silence.
Silence is our eternal speech. Silence is ever speaking. It is a perennial
flow of language which is interrupted by speaking.
